  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nGoEthereum reports \"not enough gas\" as\r\n\r\n```\r\n{'code': -32000, 'message': 'insufficient funds for gas * price + value'}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is one of the most popular error messages new blockchain developers face. ethereum.stackexchange.com alone has more than 350 questions on the topic. However, because of the vagueness of the error message, it is hard to tell what's wrong.\r\n\r\nBased on the good error message examples of Rust, etc. it should be pretty straightforward to make this error message friendlier, telling users more on the underlying reason of the problem and how to fix it.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Why should this feature exist?\r\n\r\nMake it easier for Dapp developers to enter the industry.\r\n\r\n## What are the use-cases?\r\n\r\nDevelopers can self-solve problems instead of need to ask for help.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nMode this error message to tell\r\n\r\n- What is the sufficient amount of gas GoEthereum expects\r\n- What is the available gas money on the account\r\n\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n{'code': -32000, 'message': 'Not enough ETH to send transactions. Need 0.00123 ETH, the account has 0.00123 ETH. Transaction value is 0 ETH. Gas price is 14 Gwei. The formula used to calculate the required amount is gas * price + value. '}\r\n```",
